node.text: Stunning from sunset to sunrise. An early photo of Bonita Domes in Joshua Tree (originally owned, designed, and built by Lisa Starr who used the space as her home studio and retreat before selling in 2020). Guests who visit can enjoy the domes’ shared resilience and beauty with the desert landscape that surrounds it.

node.text: Come to CalEarth and tour our domes! The "mini" Open Houses are a GREAT way for visitors of all ages to to learn about SuperAdobe technology. Our modified schedule allows for small groups (maximum 20 people per time slot) to explore our campus. Learn more: calearth.org/covid.
